The band pass filter command, bpf, is part of a group of filter commands
consisting of bpf, hpf, and lpf.  These commands invoke the sox helper
program to apply a band pass, a high pass, or a low pass filter,
respectively, to the audio.  The usual default cutoff frequencies are
300 and 3000 Hz, optimized for pitched samples (i.e., voice and music).
Only an entire audio can be filtered.
